* Diana smiled at Rion when he pulled his head out of the sand, snickering
even though she was concerned to know if he was okay.*

" You ok?"

* She reached out to brush a little of the sand away from his feathers when
he said he didn't want to play anymore, which was ok with her because the
signatures had gone.*

" Okay. Those dots on my scanners are gone anyway. Ghosts."

* She looked at him against to make sure that he was okay but fealt the heat
of the sun shining down on them and it was getting hot...so was the sand
too!
Diana looked towards the south, east, west and north, no sure where to go
now. BUT...there was some sight of land to the north and that's what they
could really use right now. Besides, maybe there was water there.
She looked at Rion again and bent down a bit.*

" Here, get on. We can go north now, see the shade?"
